(fifthQuint)Efficacy and Safety Study of TOOKAD Soluble for Localised Prostate Cancer Compared to Active Surveillance.

.

 This is a Phase 3, multicentre, open label, randomised controlled study in subjects diagnosed with low risk prostate cancer on TransRectal Ultrasound (TRUS) guided biopsy.

 Subjects will be randomised to either Active Surveillance or TOOKAD(R) Soluble VTP.

 Subjects will remain in the study for approximately 24 months following randomisation.

 A total of 400 subjects will be entered into the study; 200 will receive Active Surveillance and 200 will receive TOOKAD(R) Soluble-VTP.

